This paper deals with the impact of color constancy errors on deep neural network performance, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel augmentation method to address this problem, which involves modifying the training data to improve the robustness of the DNNs, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of pre-processing techniques to reduce the effects of incorrectly white-balanced images, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
